  "edge_hypothesis": "The Tenkan-Kijun crossover uses midpoint calculations (highest-high + lowest-low / 2) rather than exponential weighting, providing a mathematically distinct signal from all EMA-based strategies. Institutional traders use TK crosses as primary directional signals. In ranging markets (CHOP > 50), TK crosses should capture mean-reversion turns earlier than EMAs because midpoint calculations respond to range extremes rather than weighted closes. This tests whether a fundamentally different MA construction (midpoint vs exponential) produces superior signals in our best-performing regime. ITS_9 and IKS_26 have NEVER been tested in any strategy — this is first-contact with Ichimoku indicators.",
